WEBVTT

00:09.759 --> 00:12.262
You're traveling
through another dimension-

00:12.297 --> 00:16.015
a dimension not only of sight
and sound, but of mind,

00:16.050 --> 00:17.884
a journey into a wondrous land

00:17.919 --> 00:20.387
whose boundaries
are that of imagination.

00:20.422 --> 00:22.272
Your next stop,
the twilight zone.

00:26.643 --> 00:30.397
The time is 1863,
the place the state of virginia.

00:30.432 --> 00:33.533
The event is a bloodletting
known as the civil war

00:33.900 --> 00:35.151
a tragic moment in time

00:35.785 --> 00:38.905
when a nation was split
into two fragments,

00:38.940 --> 00:42.042
each fragment
deeming itself a nation.

00:42.077 --> 00:43.910
What is it?

00:43.945 --> 00:45.662
I thought
i heard something.

00:45.697 --> 00:46.913
Yanks?

00:46.948 --> 00:50.050
I don't hear 'em no more.

00:58.558 --> 01:02.312
Dauger, you figure
this would fire

01:02.347 --> 01:04.813
if you was to press
the trigger?

01:04.849 --> 01:06.066
I reckon.

01:07.934 --> 01:09.819
What's the idea,
paradine?

01:09.854 --> 01:11.071
The idea is, dauger,

01:11.106 --> 01:13.573
you ain't a right arm to me
or a left arm.

01:13.608 --> 01:15.442
You're just
some extra baggage

01:15.477 --> 01:18.578
that breathes hard
and splits my rations.

01:18.613 --> 01:21.698
You figure you'll shape up
by the end of the war?

01:21.733 --> 01:24.834
I can't help it!

01:24.869 --> 01:26.703
It used to...

01:26.738 --> 01:30.457
it used to be i never
give it any thought.

01:30.492 --> 01:31.708
It used to be like

01:31.743 --> 01:35.462
it was some kind of game
we was playing like kids.

01:35.497 --> 01:37.347
King of
the mountain.

01:37.382 --> 01:39.215
Hide and go seek.

01:39.250 --> 01:43.219
Blind man's bluff.

01:43.254 --> 01:45.722
But it ain't that way
anymore, paradine.

01:45.757 --> 01:48.224
I seen too much
of this business.

01:48.259 --> 01:50.110
I was at the second manassas.

01:58.868 --> 02:00.120
You haven't got

02:00.155 --> 02:02.622
a nerve in your body,
have you?

02:02.657 --> 02:05.125
Just as many as you, son.

02:05.160 --> 02:06.376
From head to boot.

02:06.411 --> 02:10.130
Only i don't concern myself
as much as you.

02:10.164 --> 02:11.998
You're worrying about dead men

02:12.033 --> 02:13.883
and lost battles.

02:13.918 --> 02:17.003
That's just too much area
to fret in.

02:17.038 --> 02:20.140
I'm worrying about two scouts
on a mission,

02:20.175 --> 02:23.259
and a dirty piece
of brown paper.

02:23.294 --> 02:25.762
It says the yanks are going
to take up a position

02:25.797 --> 02:27.013
in the chano valley.

02:27.048 --> 02:29.516
We got to scout them
and report back

02:29.551 --> 02:31.401
as soon as they get
into that town

02:31.436 --> 02:33.269
down there below.

